            "when": "age 28",
            "event": "When her apartment in Kochi developed a serious leak during monsoon season, she and her husband had to choose between a cheap quick-fix contractor and a more expensive but reliable one; they chose quality, stretching their budget painfully for three months.",
            "lasting_impact": "This experience cemented her belief that cutting corners on quality always costs more in the long run, even when money is tight \u2014 a tension she navigates constantly."
          },
          {
            "title": "Her Mother's Kitchen Wisdom",
            "when": "age 19",
            "event": "During a weekend visit home before moving to Kochi for her undergraduate studies, her mother walked her through how to evaluate food freshness, trusted vendors, and why the family always bought from the same neighborhood shop for decades.",
            "lasting_impact": "She internalized family as the primary source of trustworthy guidance, shaping her tendency to consult her mother or husband before making any significant household or purchase decision."
          },
          {
            "title": "Baby Arjun's First Illness",
            "when": "age 30",
            "event": "When her infant son Arjun developed a skin rash traced back to a low-cost baby product she had bought to save money, her pediatrician gently pointed out the ingredient quality difference between budget and mid-range brands.",
            "lasting_impact": "The guilt from that episode made her deeply risk-averse about product choices for her family, reinforcing her quality-first instinct even when her household budget pushes back hard."
          }
